subject: Re: Maps in Quikscript
msgSnippet: How about using the actual native s name, as well as pronunciation? For example, what we Americans call Munich is (AFAIK) Myuunchen to a local German
messageBody:
How about using the actual native's name, as well as pronunciation?
For example, what we Americans call Munich is (AFAIK) "Myuunchen" to a
local German speaker.
I have had international friends who wondered why Americans (and
the British) couldn't say the names of a few cities.
